        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Ashgrove is approximately 4 kilometres north-west of the CBD and well-connected via Waterworks Road and Ashgrove Avenue. Travel time to the CBD by car is typically 15 to 20 minutes, and the suburb is serviced by bus routes. This is one of the draws for families relocating from outer suburbs who want inner Brisbane accessibility.</p>
      </details>

